                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/243</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-22T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1918, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.06 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2073. Referring to the Legation’s No. 2072, 22d. Our British and French
                    colleagues concur in the opinion that the importation into Denmark of the
                    commodities designed to relieve Danish unemployment before the conclusion of the
                    negotiations now in progress would sensibly weaken our position and consequently
                    jeopardize their consummation.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
